# Bug Report Intake Rules

Before writing or filing, extract these fields.

| Field | Required | Notes |
|------|----------|-------|
| Portal / Product Area | Recommended | Derive from shorthand, URL, suite, or component |
| Environment | Required for filed bugs | URL/build/browser if known |
| Precondition | Required | Role, state, data setup, starting point |
| Steps to Reproduce | Required | 3–8 clear steps preferred |
| Actual Result | Required | Must be observable |
| Expected Result | Required | Must be testable |
| Test Data | Required when input matters | Use safe placeholders |
| Evidence | Required for automated mode | Screenshot strongly required for UI failures |
| Related Test Case | Recommended | Qase TC or run ID |
| Severity | Required | System impact |
| Priority | Required | Jira scheduling priority |
| Labels | Recommended | At least `qa-bug` for Jira |
| Assignee | Recommended | Current Jira user or project default |
| Sprint | Recommended | Current active sprint when available |

If Actual Result or Expected Result is missing:

- do not file
- ask for or infer from clear context only
- if inferred, mark it as inferred in the draft
- never invent expected behavior when the requirement is unclear

