# Automated Evidence-Based Bug Procedure

Use this when a failure comes from test execution or exploration.

## Required Evidence

For UI bugs, collect or reference:

- screenshot
- URL
- browser and viewport
- failing step
- actual visible result
- expected result
- console errors
- network errors
- test data used
- related Qase TC, if any

For API bugs, collect or reference:

- endpoint
- method
- request payload summary
- response status
- response body summary
- headers relevant to content type/auth
- correlation ID or trace ID, if available

For DB or data bugs, collect or reference:

- expected DB state
- actual DB state
- table or entity
- safe read-only validation query intent
- UI/API evidence showing incorrect persistence

## Evidence Quality

Evidence must be saved under:

```text
qa-artifacts/
├── screenshots/
├── console-logs/
├── network-logs/
├── traces/
├── bugs/
└── session-report.md
```

When saving a bug-specific package, use:

```text
qa-artifacts/bugs/[JIRA-KEY or bug-candidate-id]/
```

If Jira issue has not yet been created, use:

```text
qa-artifacts/bugs/BUG-CANDIDATE-[timestamp]/
```

Do not store:

- passwords
- session tokens
- API secrets
- real PII
- full sensitive request/response bodies

Redact sensitive values before attaching or referencing logs.

