# Bug Type Classification

Before filing, classify the issue.

| Classification | Meaning | Action |
|----------------|---------|--------|
| Product Defect | App behavior violates requirement or reasonable expected behavior | File bug |
| Test Case Defect | Test case expected result or steps are wrong/outdated | Update test case, do not file product bug |
| Environment Issue | Test environment, service, credentials, seed data, or config problem | File environment ticket or block tests |
| Requirement Ambiguity | Expected behavior is unclear | Ask clarification or file requirement question |
| Known Defect | Matches existing bug | Reference existing issue, do not duplicate |
| Enhancement | Behavior is inconvenient but not a defect against requirements | File improvement only if requested |

Only create a Jira Bug for Product Defect unless the team uses Bugs for environment issues.

