# Jira Description Format

Jira Cloud API v3 descriptions should be Atlassian Document Format (ADF), not Markdown, when using Jira MCP/API.

Use ADF for filed Jira issues.

Use Markdown only for draft previews shown to the user or local artifact files.

## Required Sections

Every filed bug must include:

- Precondition
- Steps to Reproduce
- Actual Result
- Expected Result

Automated evidence-based reports should also include:

- Test Data
- Environment
- Evidence / Artifacts
- Related Test Case
- Console / Network notes when useful

Manual shorthand reports may be shorter:

- Precondition
- Steps to Reproduce
- Actual Result
- Expected Result

## ADF Label Styling

When ADF is supported, style labels as:

| Label | Style |
|------|-------|
| Precondition | strong + blue `#4C9AFF` |
| Steps To Reproduce | strong + blue `#4C9AFF` |
| Actual Result | strong + red `#FF0000` |
| Expected Result | strong + green `#00875A` |
| Other labels | strong only |

Do not include raw Markdown markers like `**Actual Result**` in ADF JSON.

